<task id="004" project="ai-procedure-quality-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Inventory and schema-validate .claude/settings.json + .mcp.json</title>
    <phase>0</phase>
    <stream>inventory</stream>
    <tags>inventory, settings, schema, baseline</tags>
    <estimate>30min</estimate>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <parallel-group>0-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Validate current state of settings files against published schemas. Document any drift. This is the baseline against which the Phase 4a validator (task 060) will be tested.</goal>
    <context>The 2026-03 to 2026-05 hook-schema bug existed because no automated validation caught it. This task: (1) confirm current state is now valid after the 2026-05-14 fix, (2) document the validation procedure, (3) capture the schema URLs used.</context>
    <constraints>READ ONLY. Cannot modify the settings files in this task.</constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/settings.json</file>
      <file>.claude/settings.local.json</file>
      <file>.mcp.json</file>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read each settings file; identify the `$schema` URL it references</step>
    <step>Fetch the schema (via WebFetch); validate the JSON against it</step>
    <step>For each file: record schema URL, validation result, any warnings, any optional-field gaps</step>
    <step>If a file has no `$schema` field, note that as a finding</step>
    <step>Document the validation method (which tool, which schema URL) for use by task 060</step>
    <step>Write projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/inventory/settings-state.md</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/inventory/settings-state.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All three settings files validated; result documented</criterion>
    <criterion>Validation procedure is reproducible (someone reading the doc can re-run it)</criterion>
    <criterion>If any drift found, it's flagged with severity</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
